Q16. Find the first non-repeated character in a string.
Easy answer: Use LinkedHashMap<Character, Long> to preserve insertion order and count occurrences via streams, then return the first entry with count 1. For Unicode-heavy inputs, discuss code points instead of char.
Code / command example
public static Optional<Character> firstNonRepeated(String text) {
    Map<Character, Long> counts = text.chars()
        .mapToObj(c -> (char) c)
        .collect(Collectors.groupingBy(
            Function.identity(), LinkedHashMap::new, Collectors.counting()));

    return counts.entrySet().stream()
        .filter(e -> e.getValue() == 1)
        .map(Map.Entry::getKey)
        .findFirst();
}
// firstNonRepeated("abcab") -> Optional[c]
