Q18. SQL: find the third highest salary.
Easy answer: Use DENSE_RANK to handle ties: SELECT salary FROM (SELECT salary, DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY salary DESC) r FROM employee) x WHERE r = 3. If the interviewer asks for the employee, include employee columns and clarify tie behavior.
Code / command example
